(2003 or 2004).\n\n==Banknotes==\nA first series of banknotes was issued in November 1993. It was withdrawn from circulation by 2005. \nA second series was issued from 1998 onwards which is still in use at present.\n\n===First series (1993-1995)===\nOn 22 November 1993, banknotes of 10, 25, 50, 100, 200 and 500 dram were issued.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cba.am/ |title=Central Bank Of The Republic Of Armenia |publisher=Cba.am |date= |accessdate=30 May 2013}}</ref> \nNotes for 1,000 and 5,000 dram were put into circulation later.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 90%\"\n!colspan=\"10\"|First series (1993-1995)\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"| Image !!rowspan=\"2\"| Value !!rowspan=\"2\"| Dimensions !!rowspan=\"2\"| Main Color !!colspan=\"2\"| Description\n|-\n! Obverse !! Reverse !! Obverse !! Reverse\n|-\n| [[File:10 Armenian dram - 1993 (obverse).png|300px]]\n| [[File:10 Armenian dram - 1993 (reverse).png|300px]]\n| 10 dram\n|rowspan=\"4\"| 125 x 62&nbsp;mm\n| Brown and purple\n| Yerevan Train Station and [[David of Sasun]] statue\n|[[Mount Ararat]]\n|-\n| [[File:25 Armenian dram - 1993 (obverse).png|300px]]\n| [[File:25 Armenian dram - 1993 (reverse).png|300px]]\n| 25 dram\n| Yellow, brown and blue\n| [[Urartu|Urartian]] cuneiform tablet and a lion [[relief]] from [[Erebuni fortress]]\n| Ornaments\n|-\n| [[File:50 Armenian dram - 1993 (obverse).png|300px]]\n| [[File:50 Armenian dram - 1993 (reverse).png|300px]]\n| 50 dram\n| Blue and red\n| [[National Gallery of Armenia|National Gallery]] and [[History Museum of Armenia]]\n| [[Armenian parliament]] building\n|-\n| [[File:100 Armenian dram - 1993 (obverse).png|300px]]\n| [[File:100 Armenian dram - 1993 (reverse).png|300px]]\n| 100 dram\n| Blue, purple and red\n| [[Mount Ararat]] and [[Zvartnots Cathedral]]\n| [[Armenian Opera Theater]]\n|-\n| [[File:200 Armenian dram - 1993 (obverse).png|300px]]\n| [[File:200 Armenian dram - 1993 (reverse).png|300px]]\n| 200 dram\n|rowspan=\"2\"|135 x 62&nbsp;mm\n| Brown,green, y