e head of goddess [[Anahit]] kept in the [[British Museum]]\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Second series (1998-2017) ===\nBanknotes of 50-, 100, and 500 dram are rarely seen in circulation. The 50, 100, and 500 dram coins are used instead.<br />\nA commemorative 50,000 dram note was issued on 4 June 2001 in commemoration of the 1700th anniversary of the adoption of [[Christianity]] in [[Armenia]]. A 500 dram commemorative note was issued on 22 November 2017 to commemorate the story of Noah's Ark.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 90%\"\n!colspan=\"9\"|Second series (1998\u20132017)\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"| Image !!rowspan=\"2\"| Value !!rowspan=\"2\"| Dimensions !!rowspan=\"2\"| Main Color !!colspan=\"2\"| Description\n|-\n! Obverse !! Reverse !! Obverse !! Reverse\n|-\n| [[Image:50 Armenian dram - 1998 (obverse).png|300px]]\n| [[Image:50 Armenian dram - 1998 (reverse).png|300px]]\n| 50{{Armenian dram}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 122 x 65 &nbsp;mm\n| Pink, blue and grey\n| [[Aram Khachaturian]] and [[Armenian Opera Theater]]\n| A scene from the ballet [[Gayane (ballet)|Gayane]] by Khachaturian, and [[Mount Ararat]]\n|-\n| [[Image:100 Armenian dram - 1998 (obverse).png|300px]]\n| [[Image:100 Armenian dram - 1998 (reverse).png|300px]]\n| 100{{Armenian dram}}\n| Blue and grey\n| [[Viktor Hambardzumyan]]\n| [[Byurakan Observatory]]\n|-\n| [[Image:500 Armenian dram - 1999 (obverse).png|300px]]\n| [[Image:500 Armenian dram - 1999 (reverse).png|300px]]\n| 500{{Armenian dram}}\n| 129 x 72&nbsp;mm\n| Grey\n| [[Alexander Tamanian]]\n| [[Government House, Yerevan|Government House in Yerevan]] designed by Alexander Tamanyan\n|-\n| [[Image:1,000 Armenian dram - 1999 (obverse).png|300px]]\n| [[Image:1,000 Armenian dram - 1999 (reverse).png|300px]]\n| 1,000{{Armenian dram}}\n|136 x 72&nbsp;mm\n| Green and pink\n| [[Yeghishe Charents]]\n| An image of old [[Yerevan]] depicting the government building of the [[First Republic of Armenia|First Republic]]\n|-\n| [[Image:5,000 Armenian dram - 1999 (obverse)